        DNA damage. Using a <NUMEX TYPE="ORDINAL">Rad26</NUMEX>-GFP fusion <ENAMEX TYPE="SUBSTANCE">protein</ENAMEX>, we found that
        the nuclei of cycling cells contained, on average, <NUMEX TYPE="CARDINAL">six</NUMEX>
