        and the bright spots play a role in checkpoint-dependent
        cell cycle arrest. Furthermore, these Rad26-GFP
        localization patterns appeared normal in 
        hus1Δ , 
        rad1Δ , 
        rad9Δ , 
        rad17Δ , and 
        rad3Δ backgrounds. Therefore, Rad26
        can orchestrate early events of the DNA damage checkpoint
        <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">pathway</ENAMEX> without these <ENAMEX TYPE="SUBSTANCE">proteins</ENAMEX>, including its catalytic
        <ENAMEX TYPE="CONTACT_INFO">partner Rad3.</ENAMEX>
      
      
